---
alwaysApply: true
---
Required Configuration (Repo-wide)
nx.json (target defaults & cache)
{
  "$schema": "./node_modules/nx/schemas/nx-schema.json",
  "targetDefaults": {
    "build": { "cache": true, "outputs": ["{workspaceRoot}/dist/{projectRoot}"] },
    "test":  { "cache": true },
    "lint":  { "cache": true },
    "e2e":   { "cache": true }
  }
}


(Use targetDefaults and declare outputs to maximize cache hits.)

ESLint (flat) with Boundaries

Use the flat config from /rules/nx-sdlc.mdc in the repo root (eslint.config.mjs).

Example tsconfig.base.json (paths)
{
  "compilerOptions": {
    "baseUrl": ".",
    "paths": {
      "@mm/ads-data-access-core": ["libs/ads/data-access/core/src/index.ts"],
      "@mm/shared-ui-charts": ["libs/shared/ui/charts/src/index.ts"]
    }
  }
}


(Generators normally update this for you; verify after moves/renames.) 

Generators Defaults

Add defaults (optional) to .nx.generators.json to pre-tag libs and enforce directory/importPath conventions.

Customize or extend generators when you need opinionated scaffolds.

Caching & CI

Enable remote cache (Nx Replay) for CI; keep local cache on dev machines.

Configure provider + auth; verify with back-to-back runs and nx graph to confirm affected calc.